# Jupyterhub Service Guideline

**The jupyterhub service platform aims to provide online python jupyternotebook editor and compiler for Data science students of University of Macau.**

Please select the option you would like to refer to:
+ [Connect the UMAC private network (if necessary)](#opt1)
+ [Access the jupyterhub](#opt2)
+ [Execute your program](#opt3)
+ [Contact us](#opt4)


### <a id='opt1'>Connection to UMAC private network</a>
The Jupyterhub service system is hosted in UM private network. You could access the system directly if you are in the campus. For those who are <b>not in the UM campus</b>, please connect the UM private network through [Pulse VPN software](https://icto.um.edu.mo/network/ssl-vpn/) before you access the git service system.

![avatar][pic1]
<br>
<br>

### <a id='opt2'>Access the server</a>
After connected to UM network, you could able to access the platform by browsing [Jupyterhub Website](http://jupyter.cds.sicc.um.edu.mo:8000/). All the services are available for user who login the system. Please login the system with the account (*Not the normal UM student account) we had distributed in advance.

![avatar][pic2]
<br>
<br>

The interface is simliar to jupyternotebook, you can click the add or upload to add file or you can directly drag your program to the system

![avatar][pic3]
<br>
<br>


### <a id='opt3'>Execute your program</a>
If you are not familar with jupyternotebook You can find [tuotorial here](https://jupyter.org/), the operation here is same with jupyternotebook.
We provide basic data processing package with python 3.8.3, feel free to contact us if you require any other additional python package
